<HEADLINE> Iranian President Calls for Closer Cooperation Within ECO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad Khatami
on Saturday called for closer cooperation among member countries of
the Economic Cooperation Organization (ECO) to achieve goals of the
regional body.
</P>
<P>
He urged ECO members to cooperate actively to translate their
projects and programs into action for the realization of the goals
and aims enshrined in ECO's statute.
</P>
<P>
Addressing presidents and heads of delegations at the closing
session of the sixth ECO summit, Khatami pointed out that the one-
day meeting sent an important message to the peoples of the
regional states and the international community and presented
solutions to the economic and political issues of the organization.
</P>
<P>
The final declaration of the summit entitled the "Tehran
Declaration" includes crucial points and programs whose
implementation would help promote relationship among the regional
states, the Islamic Republic News Agency quoted Khatami as saying.
</P>
<P>
Terming ECO as "the most important and the oldest economic
establishment" in the region, he added that the body is the best
framework for creation of a regional market in line with the laws
and regulations dominating the world trade.
</P>
<P>
The Tehran-based ECO was founded by Iran, Turkey and Pakistan in
1985 and joined later by the Central Asian and Caucasian republics
of Azerbaijan, Turkmenistan, Kyrgyzstan, Uzbekistan, Tajikistan,
Kazakhstan as well as Afghanistan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
