<HEADLINE> De Bruijn Sets World Record in Women's 50-m Freestyle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Inge de Bruijn of the
Netherlands set a new world record in the women's 50 meters
freestyle when she clocked 24.39 seconds at the Brazilian swimming
championships here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
De Bruijn cut 0.09 seconds out of the former record of 24.48
that she herself set at the Dutch national championships in
Amsterdam on June 4.
</P>
<P>
De Bruijn in a world record spree on May 27-28 in Sheffield,
England set records in the women's 100 meters freestyle and the 50
meters and 100 meters butterfly and matched the then world record
of 24.51 seconds in the 50 meters freestyle.
</P>
<P>
In the last two months she has twice set world records in the
50 meters and 100 meters butterfly and the 50 meters freestyle,
and set the top world time in the 100 meters freestyle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
