<HEADLINE> Mubarak Chairs Discussion of Situation in Syria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
called a special cabinet meeting on Sunday to discuss the situation
in Syria after the death of President Hafez al-Assad.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after the meeting, Mubarak expressed shock
over the passing away of of al-Assad and highlighted their long
friendship.
</P>
<P>
"I have known President al-Assad since the days of unity between
Egypt and Syria when he was a pilot in the air force. Our relations
were very good," he said.
</P>
<P>
Egypt and Syria merged in February 1958 to form the United Arab
Republic (UAR). Syria seceded from the UAR in September 1961.
Mubarak underwent military training with al-Assad in the 1960s in
Moscow.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak lauded the Egyptian-Syrian ties and cooperation as time-
honoured, strong and close in various domains.
</P>
<P>
He pledged support for the coming leadership in Syria.
</P>
<P>
"We respect the Syrian people's way of choosing their president
and wish Syria stability and security because it is a pivotal
country" in the region, he said.
</P>
<P>
Al-Assad, 69, died of a heart attack Saturday morning.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak said Saturday al-Assad's death was "an enormous loss for
the Syrian people and the nation." He ordered three days of
mourning for al-Assad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
