<DOCNO> XIE20000611.0017 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Syria Sets Tuesday for Assad's Funeral Procession 1st lead-writethru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, June 11 (Xinhua) -- A funeral procession for the late
Syrian president Hafez Al-Assad will take place on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The procession will start at 0800 a.m. local time on Tuesday.
The coffin will be carried from the residence in which he lived
during the past three decades to Omaiya Square in Damascus.
</P>
<P>
In Omaiya Square, a huge popular farewell will be given to the
late president and the Syrian people will express their love for
Assad and their profound grief for his loss.
</P>
<P>
The official funeral procession will move slowly behind the
coffin which will be carried on a military carriage decorated with
the Syrian national flag.
</P>
<P>
The coffin will be escorted by a host of soldiers representing
all branches of the Syrian armed forces, from Omaiya Square to the
People's Palace where the mourners will give their last farewell
look at their leader.
</P>
<P>
At 0300 p.m. local time, the procession will move from the
People's Palace to Maza airport near Damascus where the corpse will
be carried to the airport of Basil Assad in Latakia.
</P>
<P>
At Basil airport, and along the road leading to Qardaha town,
the home town of the late president, a popular reception will be
held.
</P>
<P>
The corpse of the late Syrian president will then be carried on
a military carriage to lady Nassa's mosque where it will be laid
out.
</P>
<P>
After Asar prayers and funeral prayers, burial ceremonies will
start and the deceased will be laid to the rest in his family's
cemetery.
</P>
<P>
