<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chronology of Bomb Blasts in Western Cape, South Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 11 (Xinhua) -- A bomb blast which injured
two people in Cape Town, South Africa, on Saturday night has been
the latest in a string of blasts at a public places in Western
Cape during the past two years.
</P>
<P>
The following is a chronology of the most blasts in the region.
</P>
<P>
June 26, 1998: A pipe bomb exploded outside the Mowbray police
station -- no one was injured;
</P>
<P>
August 6, 1998: A street vendor died and another was injured in
a blast in Belville outside the building housing the special
police task team probing People Against Gangsterism and Drugs;
</P>
<P>
August 25, 1998: Two people were killed and 26 others injured
in a blast at the Planet Hollywood restaurant at the Victoria and
Alfred Waterfront;
</P>
<P>
December 18, 1998: Wynberg synagogue was bombed -- no one was
injured;
</P>
<P>
January 1, 1999: Car bomb injured two at the Waterfront;
</P>
<P>
January 8, 1999: A Kentucky Fried Chicken branch in Athlone was
petrol- bombed;
</P>
<P>
January 28, 1999: A bomb injured 11 outside Caledon Square
police headquarters;
</P>
<P>
January 30, 1999: A woman was injured and a police car
destroyed in a blast at the Woodstock police station;
</P>
<P>
May 9, 1999: A car bomb exploded outside Athlone police
station;
</P>
<P>
November 6, 1999: Nine people were injured in a blast at the
gay Blah Bar in Somerset Road in central Cape Town;
</P>
<P>
November 28, 1999: 48 people were injured in a blast at St
Elmo's restaurant in Camps Bay;
</P>
<P>
December 24, 1999: Seven police officers were injured by a bomb
planted in a refuse bin outside Mano's restaurant in Main Road,
Greenpoint. The blast was triggered remotely by cellphone;
</P>
<P>
January 12, 2000: A bomb attached to a motorbike exploded in
front of the Wynberg Magistrate's Court, leaving at least one
person injured;
</P>
<P>
May 22, 2000: Police deactivated a pipe bomb outside the New
York Bagels and Sitdown, in Seapoint, after the device was
discovered by two vagrants;
</P>
<P>
June 10, 2000: Two people were slightly injured when a bomb,
placed inside a Toyota Corolla, detonated outside the New York
Bagels and Sitdown restaurant. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
