<HEADLINE> Iran Stresses Regional Cooperation in Facing Globalization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal
Kharrazi said here on Sunday Central Asian and Caucasian countries
should bolster cooperation to face challenges brought about by the
globalization process.
</P>
<P>
Iran believes regional countries should enhance and
institutionalize cooperation to take advantage of the opportunities
and deal with the challenges of globalization, Kharrazi said at an
international seminar on the Central Asian and the Caucasus region.
</P>
<P>
He said Iran is the best route to set up a pipeline linking
landlocked countries in Central Asia to the outside world so that
their rich oil and gas resources could be transported to the
international market.
</P>
<P>
Experts believe the pipeline through Iran is the shortest, the
cheapest and the safest for the Central Asian and the Caucasian
states to the international market, he said.
</P>
<P>
None of the countries in the region has the capability and the
technology that Iran has in shipment and export of oil, he added.
</P>
<P>
Elsewhere in his speech, the minister reiterated a legal regime
acceptable to all should be established among countries bordering
the Caspian Sea so that these states could cooperate in developing
and utilizing resources in the region.
</P>
<P>
He said Iran has given number one priority to develop diplomatic
relations with its northern neighbors in the Central Asian region
and will follow the same policy in the future.
</P>
<P>
Over 160 experts from 32 countries are taking part in the two-
day seminar which started Sunday under the sponsorship of the
Institute of Political and International Studies affiliated to the
Iranian Foreign Ministry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
