</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference, Wapakabulo said: "Following six
days of the senseless carnage and mayhem of the Rwandan People
Army (RPA) in Kisangani, it becomes abundantly clear that the RPA
was not interested in a cease-fire."
</P>
<P>
He said the RPA had frustrated the bilateral arrangement for
simultaneous withdrawal on Monday and the unilateral cease-fire
and withdrawal proposed by Uganda on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"The RPA had also frustrated the multilateral agreement reached
by the presidents of Uganda and Rwanda with the assistance of the
U.N. and the U.S. government on the afternoon of June 8," said
Wapakabulo.
</P>
<P>
He confirmed that four officers of the Uganda People's Defence
Forces (UPDF) were killed when they tried to negotiate the
multilateral cease-fire ordered by the June 8 tele-conference,
saying that the murder of the four UPDF officers in the process of
implementing the multilateral cease-fire arrangement lies squarely
at the hands of Rwandan government.
</P>
<P>
The RPA in Kisangani, the third largest city of the DRC, is
insensitive to the massive deaths of civilians and destruction of
property as it is continuously using Congolese people as human
shields in flagrant disregard of all international Conventions,
said Wapakabulo.
</P>
<P>
Wapakabulo accused the governments of Rwanda and the DRC of
undermining and frustrating the implementation of the Lusaka
Cease-fire Agreement, saying that this must be exposed and
condemned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
