<HEADLINE> German President Praises Assad as "Major Interlocutor" in Mideast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BERLIN, June 11 (Xinhua) -- German President Johannes Rau, in
a condolence message released Sunday, praised the late Syrian
President Hafez al-Assad, who died on Saturday, as a statesman who
decisively influenced events in the whole Middle East.
</P>
<P>
"He was a major interlocutor for all who were concerned with
the Middle East peace process," said Rau in a telegram to Syrain
Prime Minister Mohammed Mustafa Miro. The message was released by
the presidential office in Berlin.
</P>
<P>
Rau said that al-Assad had attained great respects and
recognition in recent times and great expectations had been put in
him that he would enable a breakthrough to peace. "Those
expectations will still be placed in Syria following his death,"
Rau said.
</P>
<P>
German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder sent a condolence letter
to Miro on Saturday. He said in the letter that "President Hafez
al-Assad will not be forgotten." "He shaped and left a decisive
mark on the history of the Middle East and the Arab world," he
said. 
</P>
