<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy Beats Turkey 2-1 with Controversial Penalty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Italy beat Turkey 2-1 in a Euro
2000 Group B match in the Dutch city of Arnhem on Sunday thanks
only to a controversial penalty awarded to and scored by striker
Filippo Inzaghi in the 70th minute.
</P>
<P>
Inzaghi went down in the penalty area as he and Turkish captain
Temizkenoglu Ogun were chasing a through ball. Scottish referee
Hugh Dallas ruled that Inzaghi had been elbowed before fell.
After the referee had no hesitation in pointing to the spot,
enraged Turkish fans pelted the pitch with plastic bottles and
other objects.
</P>
<P>
Italy had taken the lead in the 52nd minute when Juventus
midfielder Antonio Conte scored with an acrobatic overhead kick
just outside the goal area after a cross by Inzaghi cross was only
partially cleared by Alpay Ozalan.
</P>
<P>
Turkey equalized the score nine minutes later when unmarked
diminutive Galatasary midfielder Okan Buruk headed home a Sergen
Yalcin free kick. It was Turkey's first ever goal at a European
Championship finals. They failed to score in their only other
previous appearance in the finals four years ago.
</P>
<P>
Dino Zoff's side made a furious start to the match and the
Italians won seven corners in the first 14 minutes.
</P>
<P>
After their victories in their respective opening games,
Belgium and Italy are jointly top of Group B with three points and
same goal difference.
</P>
<P>
Belgium beat Sweden 2-1 in Brussels on Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
