<HEADLINE> Former ROK President Supports China's Western Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 11 (Xinhua)-- Roh Tae-woo, former president of
the Republic of Korea (ROK), said today that he will do his best
to encourage the ROK government and businesses to participate in
China's western development.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with Nie Ronggui, chairman of the Sichuan
provincial committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference, Roh Tae-woo said that he had seen a lot
of changes compared to his first trip to China eight years ago.
</P>
<P>
He said that the ROK government and business community are very
much concerned about China's strategies to develop its western
regions. He said that the bilateral ties between the two countries,
especially the trade relations, have been progressing well since
1992.
</P>
<P>
Nie briefed the guest on developments in Sichuan Province,
strategies for western development, and ROK's investment in the
Province. 
