<HEADLINE> Top Chinese Leader on Urban Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Top Chinese leader Li Ruihuan has
urged senior officials and experts from 150 Chinese cities to
better improve the management of urban development.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to the officials and experts at the Fourth Session
of the China Urban Development Society, Li said China should make
all efforts to learn from overseas countries. Detailed studies
should also be done to explore further and improve the management
of China's urban development.
</P>
<P>
Li, member of the Standing Committee of the Chinese Communist
Party Central Committee, said as China continues to modernize, the
general public place more demands on its cities. It is crucial
that measures are implemented to improve urban management,
beautify the environment and improve the educational level of the
urban population. The three-day meeting will conclude tomorrow in
Shenzhen, in the southern province of Guangdong.  
