in Syria in 20 years, during which the bilateral ties stalled
because of Syria's support for Tehran in the 1980-1988 Iraq-Iraq
war.
</P>
<P>
But the political ice began to thaw in 1997 when the borders
between the two countries were reopened for bilateral trade.
