<HEADLINE> OAU Chief Meets Chinese Deputy FM on Bejing Forum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
by Zhao Yi
</P>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Secretary General Salim Ahmed
Salim of the Organization of African Unity (OAU) met Chinese
Deputy Foreign Minister Ji Peiding here Sunday on a
comprehensive agreement over "China and Africa Cooperation Forum"
 scheduled to be held in Beijing on October 10-12.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, Ji briefed Salim on the purpose of holding
the ministerial level forum. The two sides also introduced the
agenda and main contents of the documents to be adopted at the
forum.
</P>
<P>
Ji noted that the OAU is an organization that has played an
extremely important role in striving for independence and
liberation of Africa and for the peace and development process in
the continent.
</P>
<P>
The OAU has also made positive contribution to promote
friendship and cooperation between China and Africa, Ji said,
stressing China attaches great importance to the unique role and
influence by the OAU in African and international affairs.
</P>
<P>
The OAU's support for China and Africa Cooperation Forum and
its participation in the forum is of great importance to the
success of the international meeting, Ji added.
</P>
<P>
In response, Salim said that being a friend of Africa, China
has been supporting national independence, political liberation
and economic development of Africa.
</P>
<P>
It is of great significance to promote cooperation between
Africa and China when a new international order is being
established in the new century, he said.
</P>
<P>
Salim said China and Africa Cooperation Forum, which was
suggested on the occasion of great changes taking place in the
world, and of Africa facing challenges of globalization, will
provide the participants with an important opportunity for a
collective dialogue.
</P>
<P>
The OAU secretary general has accepted China's invitation to
participate in the forum.
</P>
<P>
Ji arrived here Saturday for a three-day working visit.
</P>
</TEXT>
