<DOCNO> XIE20000611.0076 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 4 Million UK Children live in Poverty: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Up to four million UK children are
trapped in poverty, according to a United Nations report.
</P>
<P>
The report says Britain has one of the worst records on
childhood poverty in the industrialized world, the Observer
newspaper reported on Sunday, quoting the U.N. report as saying.
</P>
<P>
U.N. children's fund UNICEF estimates that nearly 20 percent of
young people live in UK families below the official poverty line --
with the household income below half median earnings.
</P>
<P>
UNICEF said the UK's 20 percent of young people living in
families below the poverty line compared to less than 5 percent in
Sweden, Norway and Finland.
</P>
<P>
The UK also falls short of standards in Turkey, Poland and
Hungary, the report said.
</P>
<P>
It also remains stuck in the bottom quarter of the world's
child poverty league when it is judged on absolute poverty --
where household income is below the U.S. official poverty line.
</P>
<P>
It came 14th out of 19 inspected countries, just above Italy,
according to the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
