<HEADLINE> Putin Condoles Over Syrian President's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MOSCOW, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Vladimir Putin
expressed "sincere and deep condolences to the people and
leadership of the Syrian Arab Republic on the unfortunate death of
President Hafez al-Assad," a Kremlin spokesman said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Assad was "one of the most outstanding figures of today who
played a historic role in Syria's development," and his death is a
"heavy loss to the people of friendly Syria," Putin said in his
message to Damascus.
</P>
<P>
Assad was "a friend of our country who made a great
contribution to the development of the Russian-Syrian cooperation,
" Putin said.
</P>
<P>
However, the Kremlin ruled out the possibility of Putin's
presence at Assad's funeral.
</P>
<P>
"Russia will be represented at the funeral of Syrian President
Hafez Assad at an appropriate level," and "the cancellation or
postponement of President Vladimir Putin's visit to Spain,
scheduled for June13-14, is out of the question," the Itar-Tass
news agency quoted the Kremlin spokesman as saying.
</P>
<P>
Assad, 70, who had been suffering from heart problems, died
Saturday. He was born on October 6, 1930 and became head of state
of Syria in 1971. His funeral is scheduled for June 13. Putin is
due to leave for Spain the same day. 
</P>
