<DOCNO> XIE20000611.0094 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Small Hi-tech Firms Receive Support for Technological Innovations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Small high-tech firms in China are
receiving intensified State support to technological innovation
efforts, an official of the Ministry of Technology said.
</P>
<P>
The special fund set up by the Torch Center of the Ministry of
Technology last year, which is devoted to financing technological
innovations in medium-size and small high-tech firms in China, has
aided 759 such projects since last year with a total of 550
million yuan, said Li Linxi, chief engineer of the Torch Center.
</P>
<P>
Another 300 projects received low-interest loans totaling 260
million yuan, he added.
</P>
<P>
Upon completion, the above projects, mainly in areas such as
electronics, new materials, bio-medicine, and new energy, will
help generate 33 billion yuan in industrial added-value and 1.23
billion US dollars in export turnover, Li said.
</P>
<P>
More than 3,300 projects are still on the waiting list for aid
from the special fund for technological innovations in small and
hi-tech firms, calling for about four billion yuan in total.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that China now has over ten million medium-size
and small enterprises, accounting for more than 97 percent of the
total enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The government will continue to increase its support to small
enterprises with their own intellectual patents, high technology,
and good market prospects, Li stressed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
