<HEADLINE> First Tip for Hazardous Industrial Garbage in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The first tip for dangerous
industrial garbage in China has been built in this capital city of
northeastern China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
With an area of 130,000 sq. meters, the tip is designed to
handle 20,000 tons of nocuous solid garbage annually and can
accept such dangerous items as metals, acid or alkaline garbage
for up to 12 years with a total handling capacity of 240,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Built with 6.44 million US dollars in world bank loans and 84
million yuan of Chinese counterpart fund, the tip was meant to be
a demonstration project for similar projects in other Chinese
cities. 
</P>
