<HEADLINE> Manila Hotel Receives Bomb Threats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The Manila Grand Hotel received two
bomb threats on Sunday, one day before the Independence Day rites
at the nearby Rizal Park, but police found no explosives in the
hotel.
</P>
<P>
The first bomb threat took place in the morning and the second
occurred in the afternoon, the Philippine News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
In both cases Manila anti-bomb experts checked the hotel for
any bomb but didn't find any explosives, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Rizal Park police detachment said that the Rizal
Park is peaceful and orderly, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
In the past several weeks, the Philippine capital was hit by a
string of bombings. The authorities blamed Moslem rebels for the
bombing incidents and arrested 26 suspects. 
</P>
