<HEADLINE> Singapore Police Make Biggest Seizure of Psychotropic Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 11 ( Xinhua) -- The Singapore authorities have
seized illegal mind altering drugs worth 560,000 Singapore dollars
(about 326,000 U.S. dollars), the biggest haul of psychotropic
drugs so far in the city-state, newspapers here reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese newspaper IANHE ZAOBAO reported that Singapore's
Central Narcotics Bureau (CNB) recovered 26,000 Erimin tablets, 9,
592 Upjohn tablets, more than 1,000 Ecstasy and Ice tablets from a
room in a second-storey apartment in a raid named Operation Rumble,
on Friday which netted 16 suspected drug offenders, all
Singaporean men.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Sunday Times reported that the CNB has raided
more than 30 nightspots and entertainment outlets in the past two
months to flush out drug offenders and rounded up 97 lounge
hostesses for offenses ranging from possession and consumption of
drugs to trafficking.
</P>
<P>
It has noted that a worrying trend -- syndicates are using KTV
lounge hostesses to push drugs, the paper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
