<HEADLINE> Iranian Leaders Condole on Assad's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Iranian supreme leader Ayatollah Ali
Khamenei and President Mohammad Khatami on Saturday night sent
messages to express their condolences over the death of late Syrian
President Hafez al-Assad.
</P>
<P>
In his message to Bashar, the favorite son of Assad, Khamenei
said the late Syrian president was one of the most prominent
figures in the Arab and Islamic world, and had rendered great
services during his life to the Syrian nation and the Arab world.
</P>
<P>
Assad died of a heart attack on Saturday at age 69.
</P>
<P>
"No doubt, President Assad was a pivot of resistance among
frontline states and an important factor in saving the line of
resistance against defeats vis-a-vis the Zionists (Israelis) and
their allies," Khamenei said, quoted by the official Islamic
Republic News Agency on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei praised Assad for his role in consolidating the Arab
and Muslim world and his efforts to expand relations with Iran.
Assad "had rightfully recognized that the establishment of an
Islamic government in Iran had tipped the balance of power in favor
of the revolutionary forces of the Muslim world," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also assured that the Iranian government will continue to
stand by the side of the Syrian government and Syrian nation.
</P>
<P>
President Khatami also praised Assad as an outstanding leader in
the Islamic world who had played an important role in resistance
against Israeli expansionist policies and "developments in the
region."
</P>
<P>
Syria was among the few supporters of Iran in its 1980-88 bloody
war with Iraq, in which some 1 million people from both sides died.
</P>
<P>
The government in Tehran is against the peace process with the
Jewish state, which it doesn't recognize, and vows to support the
efforts to liberate all the territories occupied by Israel.
</P>
</TEXT>
