<HEADLINE> Hatakeyama Become WBA lightweight Champion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
TOKYO, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Former champion Takanori Hatakeyama
became the new World Boxing Association (WBA) lightweight titlist
on Sunday after knocking out title holder Gilberto Serrano of
Venezuela on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The knock-out came two minutes 30 seconds into the eighth
round when the Japanese challenger sent the defending champion
down for a third time in the round and a fifth time overall to
finish off the fight, according to reports.
</P>
<P>
Hatakeyama, ranked 10th in the WBA, also floored Serrano once
each in the fifth round and seventh round.
</P>
<P>
It was the first bout for Hatakeyama since he was beaten in
his defence of the WBA super featherweight title to Lakva Sim of
Mongolia in Tokyo just one year ago.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old new champion stretched his record to 23 wins,
including 18 KOs, against one defeat and two draws.
</P>
<P>
For Serrano, 30, stretched his record to 20 wins, including 17
KOs, against four defeats and two draws. 
