<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kathmandu Prone to Quake Damage: Experts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Faulty construction of houses in
the Kathmandu Valley could be a major cause of severe losses of
life and property in the event of a quake hitting the valley,
according to Nepali experts.
</P>
<P>
The experts are gathering here Sunday to discuss steps to
reduce damages by such disasters as earthquakes.
</P>
<P>
"Kathmandu tops the list of cities that are earthquake-prone,"
said Amod Dixit, an intellectual.
</P>
<P>
Dixit cautioned the residents in the valley to prepare
themselves to mitigate disasters caused by an earthquake which has
every possibility of happening within coming years.
</P>
<P>
Murari Gautam, member-secretary of the Kathmandu Disaster
Management Committee, said the wards in the valley needed to be
divided into a number of clusters to be better equipped to face
the challenge of earthquakes.
</P>
<P>
Other measures discussed at the meeting include launching
awareness programs among residents, strengthening old buildings,
study of school buildings and training of teachers, parents and
students to prepare for any eventuality. 
</P>
</TEXT>
