<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT, June 11 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA -- The five countries that form the Community of Andean
Nations (CAN) must unite to face the globalization process the
world is undergoing, said economist Washington Herrera in Lima
Saturday, during the 12th Andean Presidential Summit.
</P>
<P>
This subregional meeting being held in the Peruvian capital on
June 9-10 is attended by the presidents of Colombia, Andres
Pastrana, Hugo Banzer of Bolivia, Gustavo Noboa of Ecuador, Hugo
Chavez of Venezuela, and Alberto Fujimori of Peru. (Andean
Countries-Globalization)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iranian President Mohammad Khatami Saturday called
for closer cooperation among member countries of the Economic
Cooperation Organization (ECO) to achieve goals of the regional
body.
</P>
<P>
He urged ECO members to cooperate actively to translate their
projects and programs into action for the realization of the goals
and aims enshrined in ECO's statute. (Iran-President-ECO)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
HAVANA -- Cuban President Fidel Castro considered "an important
step" the project to be analyzed next week by the United States
Congress to authorize the sale of food and medicines to this
Caribbean island.
</P>
<P>
"I see it as a beginning, as a necessary step to continue with
what must be the only just, the only correct action, which is the
end of the economic embargo," imposed by the United States to the
island in 1962, said Castro Saturday. (Cuba-US-Food)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ROME -- Italian Premier Giuliano Amato and his Spanish
counterpart Jose' Maria Aznar closed their two-day summit in Italy
's southern city of Naples expressing common satisfaction over the
state of bilateral relations, voicing their readiness to boost
both collaboration and cooperation and agreeing that this summit,
the sixth since 1995, was more "fruitful" than the others.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the closing joint press conference, Amato said the
summit was "very satisfying" and allowed for a "convergence of
views on concrete issues and specific questions". (Italy-Spain-
Cooperation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LIMA -- The 12th Andean Presidential Summit concluded Saturday
with the commitment of the presidents of five regional countries
to establish the Andean Common Market in 2005.
</P>
<P>
The Andean leaders promised in the Lima Declaration issued at
the end of the two-day meeting to strengthen democracy and the war
against poverty, social exclusion, corruption, and drug
trafficking in the bloc. (Andean Summit-Economy)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- The Thai government will not start to repay the
bailout loan it received from the International Monetary Fund (IMF)
during the economic crisis before schedule, Prime Minister Chuan
Leekpai was quoted by Thai News Agency as saying Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"The government had yet talked about the issue, but had decided
to stop to withdraw further funds from the IMF's rescue package,"
he said. (Thailand-IMF-Loan) 
</P>
