<HEADLINE> Ziliute Beats Longo in Women's Challenge Third Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Diana Ziliute of Lithuania
extended her race lead over Australia's Anna Wilson on Saturday
night by capturing the 46-kilometer Elkhorn Circuit Race in Idaho,
third stage of the Women's Challenge cycling event.
</P>
<P>
Ziliute, the reigning women's Tour de France champion, beat
defending champion Jeannie Longo of France by completing the 18-
lap course in one hour, 17 minutes and eight seconds.
</P>
<P>
Longo finished second with an identical time. American Karen
Kurren was third, five seconds behind the leading duo.
</P>
<P>
The Lithuanian, who assumed the overall lead after her second
consecutive second-place finish on Friday, gained a 10-second time
bonus for the stage win and other mid-race bonus time.
</P>
<P>
Because of various lapped riders and complicated bonus time
calculations, officials were unable to immediately produce
official overall standings.
</P>
<P>
The field in the 11-day, 1,007-kilometer race through Idaho
will face its most difficult stage Sunday -- the 93.6-kilometer
Rupert to Pomerelle road race, which includes an 18-kilometre
ascent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
