<HEADLINE> Weekly Review of Regional News In China (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI:
</P>
<P>
-- China's first newspaper for Internet lovers appeared in this
largest industrial center in China. Internet users in China topped
8.9 million by the end of last year, with the figure tripling
annually, statistics show.
</P>
<P>
-- The Shanghai Volkswagen Corp. announced on June 6 the
launching of the company's Passat Sedan on the Chinese market. The
new sedan is the third generation of sedan produced by the
Shanghai Volkswagen Corp. after the Santana and the Santana 2000.
</P>
<P>
GUANGZHOU: Construction of the terminal building of New
Guangzhou Baiyun Airport has begun in Huadu City of Guangdong
Province. Supporting facilities such as a special highway
connecting the construction site, power and water supply
facilities are ready in service, and the construction of two
control towers also started.
</P>
<P>
HEBEI: A museum to resemble the Japanese watch tower in China
during the War of Resistance Against Japan (1937-1945), was set up
entirely by farmers in northern Hebei Province near the site of
the then Tunnel Warfare in Ranzhuang, Qingyuan County, where local
people defeated the Japanese troops in underground tunnels.
</P>
</TEXT>
