<HEADLINE> Weekly Review of Regional News In China (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 11 (Xinhua) -- The following is a weekly review of
major regional news in China from June 4 to June 10.
</P>
<P>
BEIJING:
</P>
<P>
-- A meeting of the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS) and the
Chinese Academy of Engineering (CAE) opened on June 5, which
focused on China's scientific and technological development in the
21st century.
</P>
<P>
-- Beijing hosted a symposium on implementing a law to curb
juvenile delinquency on June 5.
</P>
<P>
-- More than 1,000 auto and parts manufacturers from some 20
countries and regions participated in the Auto China 2000 expo,
which opened in Beijing on June 6.
</P>
<P>
-- China has launched its first securities WAP (wireless
application protocol) website in Beijing at www.158china.com. The
website now provides WAP cellular phone users access to financial
news, instant stock quotes, commentary and stock market advice.
</P>
<P>
-- The Beijing Intellectual Property Right Bureau was
officially founded on June 8. The aim of establishing the bureau
is to meet the needs of China's impending entry into the World
Trade Organization and the development of a knowledge-based
economy.
</P>
