<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pedroso Wins Men's Long Jump in Turin Athletics Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Cuban long jump legend Ivan Pedroso
and Australia's two time 400m world champion Cathy Freeman won
their respective events golds at the IAAF Grand Prix at the new
Primo Nebiolo stadium in Turin, Italy on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
27-year-old Pedroso, who is also a four-time world indoor long
jump champion, cleared 8.39 meters for the champion.
</P>
<P>
James Beckford of Jamaica finished second with 8.20, followed
by russian Vladimir Maliavin with 8.17.
</P>
<P>
The Olympic silver medalist Freeman won the women's 400m race
in 51.20 seconds, beating Jamaica' rival Sandie Richards, who
clocked 51.38.
</P>
<P>
The men's 100m champion went to Nigerian Deji Aliu who timed in
10.17 while Bahamas' Pauline Davis won the women's 200m in 23.12.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
