<HEADLINE> China Mourns Passing Away of Assad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government expressed
its deep condolences over the passing away of Syrian President
Hafez al-Assad who died of disease on Saturday, Chinese Foreign
Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao said here today in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that President Assad was the outstanding leader of
Syria who has contributed all his life to the development of the
country and the happiness of the Syrian people.
</P>
<P>
President Assad valued Syria-China ties, he added.
</P>
<P>
The passing away of the president is a great loss to the Syrian
people, Zhu said, adding that the Chinese people also lost a
respected friend.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government believes that Syria will march forward
along the path set by President Assad, and Sino-Syrian ties will
continue to advance, Zhu said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
