<BODY>
<HEADLINE> WHO Warns of Fast Spread of TB in Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The World Health Organization (
WHO) has warned of fast spread of Tuberculosis (TB) in the Afghan
province of Badghis.
</P>
<P>
Health authorities feared that if immediate assistance would
not be provided, one-third of the people of the area would become
TB patients, according to a report of the Associated Press of
Pakistan (APP) Saturday.
</P>
<P>
They said that poverty was the main reason of the fast spread
of TB, meanwhile the use of unhygienic milk and ignorance about
health services also caused this disease.
</P>
<P>
The local branch of WHO in Herat said it would soon open a
clinic for TB patients in Badghis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
