<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Huge Quantity of Hashish Seized in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Balochistan Custom
recovered around eleven tons of hashish near Rakhni a couple of
days ago and arrested five people, the Associated Press of
Pakistan (APP) reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The report said that four trucks loaded with hollow iron pipes
were intercepted near Rakhni when they were on their way to Punjab.
Examination and drilling of one of the pipes revealed that it was
filled with hashish. It was estimated that 11 tons of hashish were
being carried in the pipes.
</P>
<P>
Further investigation was in progress. 
</P>
</TEXT>
