<HEADLINE> Swedish Prime Minister Pays Homage to Assad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Swedish Prime Minister Goran
Persson Saturday paid homage to Syrian President Hafez al-Assad,
saying that he played a key role in the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, Persson described Assad as an "outstanding
figure" in the political life of the Middle East and praised him
for his "decisive role" in the peace process.
</P>
<P>
One of Assad's greatest achievements is the Syrian-Israeli
agreement on Golan Heights, said Persson.
</P>
<P>
Persson said Assad's death will bring about new changes to
Syria and the rest of the Middle East and hoped Syria's new leader
could play a new role and continue the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Assad died of a heart attack Saturday morning after 30 years in
power. He was 69. 
</P>
</TEXT>
