<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Inter-Korean Summit Delayed by One Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The summit between leaders of South
Korea and the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) has
been delayed by one day until Tuesday, said a South Korean
presidential spokesman on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The delay was requested by the DPRK for technical reasons, the
spokesman said. Pyongyang asked for more time to prepare.
</P>
<P>
The historic three-day summit between South Korean President
Kim Dae-jung and DPRK leader Kim Jong Il was originally scheduled
to start on Monday in Pyongyang. Now the summit will be held from
Tuesday to Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The summit will be the first ever since the Korean peninsular
was divided in the Korean War in the early 1950s. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
