<HEADLINE> Inter-Korean Summit Delayed by One Day EDS-ADDS more quotes of spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The summit between leaders of South
Korea and the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) has
been postponed for one day until Tuesday, said a South Korean
presidential spokesman on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
President Kim Dae-jung's visit to Pyongyang will begin Tuesday,
a day later than originally scheduled, to continue through
Thursday for two days and three nights, said spokesman Park Joon-
young.
</P>
<P>
Through a telephone message late Saturday night, the DPRK
requested the rescheduling of the summit due to "technical matters,
" Park said.
</P>
<P>
When asked to elaborate on what Pyongyang referred to "
technical matters," the spokesman said, "I think it is just
because of preparatory issues."
</P>
<P>
The summit will be the first ever since the division of the
Korean peninsular after World War II.
</P>
<P>
An agreement on the summit was reached by the two sides in
Beijing in April. 
</P>
</TEXT>
