<HEADLINE> Kaizer Chiefs Wins South African Super Bowl </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 10 (Xinhua) -- A 44th minute penalty by
Siyabonga Nomvete gave Kaizer Chiefs a 1-0 victory over Mamelodi
Sundowns in the South African Super Bowl soccer cup final on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The penalty came after Namibia international Robert Nauseb was
tripped by Sundowns' midfielder Charles Motlohi.
</P>
<P>
Chiefs, the country's most popular club, had not won the trophy
for eight years.
</P>
<P>
Defeat robbed Sundowns of a unique triple, having won the
league championship last month and the League Cup in December.
</P>
</TEXT>
