<HEADLINE> Cipollini Crashed in Cycling Practice </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Italian sprinter Mario Cipollini
crashed in practice on Saturday, putting his prospects for next
month's Tour de France at risk, his Saeco team said.
</P>
<P>
The Tour de France race begins on July 1.
</P>
<P>
Cipollini went out for a training ride after winning a night
race in Florence on Friday, but took a bump in the road badly and
smashed his chin in the fall.
</P>
<P>
Passers-by took him to hospital, where he had 30 stitches. He
returned to hospital later, still in pain, and was found to have
two cracked ribs and some jaw problems. 
</P>
</TEXT>
