<HEADLINE> Earthquake Jolts Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 6.8 on the
Richter scale rocked central Taiwan at 02:23 (Beijing time) today,
according to the State Seismological Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The quake was felt all over the island, with the epicenter at
the county of Nantou.
</P>
<P>
Several aftershocks have been recorded.
</P>
<P>
Seismologists said today's quake was an aftershock of the
powerful earthquake on September 21 last year, which killed more
than 2,000 people and injured another 8,139.
</P>
<P>
There have been reports of injuries. 
</P>
