<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Leaves for European, Asian Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of China's
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, left here
this morning by a special plane to start an official good-will
visit to six European and Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
The six countries are the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia, the
Republic of Slovenia, the Republic of Croatia, the Slovak Republic,
the Republic of Azerbaijan, and Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
Li is invited by the parliaments and governments of the those
countries.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Li will confer with leaders of governments
and parliaments of these countries to promote the healthy
development of relations between China and the six countries.
</P>
<P>
