<HEADLINE> Cuesta Wins Sixth Stage in Dauphine Libere Cycle Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Spaniard Inigo Cuesta won the 218-
kilometer sixth stage of the Dauphine Libere from Digne to
Briancon on Saturday -- a section to be used in the Tour de France
next month.
</P>
<P>
Cuesta clocked six hours 22 minutes 40 seconds, 19 seconds
ahead of his compatriot Pablo Lastras.
</P>
<P>
The most demanding stage of this year's Dauphine Libere cycle
race followed almost exactly the same route as the Tour's stage on
July 15.
</P>
<P>
American Tyler Hamilton retained overall leadership by
registering 26 hours 49 minutes 37 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Spaniard Haimar Zubeldia was second with 31 seconds behind. And
Lance Armstrong of the United States came in third with 36 seconds
behind. 
</P>
