<HEADLINE> Pace and Johansen Advance to Match Tour Semi-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, June 10 (Xinhua) -- French America's Cup skipper
Bertrand Pace and Dane Jesper Radich Johansen advanced to the semi-
finals of the Volvo Lake Constance 2000 Match Racing Regatta,
fourth event on the Swedish Match Tour, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
But violent thunder storms delayed the quarter-finals between
Australians Peter Gilmour and Neville Wittey, and Frenchman Luc
Pillot against Magnus Holmberg of Sweden until Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Pace defeated Poland's Karol Jablonski by two races to one,
while Radich Johansen dealt a similar fate to Team New Zealand's
Hamish Pepper.
</P>
<P>
In a light but steady morning breeze both the Frenchman and the
Dane won their opening quarter-final matches but Jablonski and
Pepper levelled the score in the second confrontations.
</P>
<P>
Pace and Johansen won their deciding matches against their
respective rivals.
</P>
<P>
With the other two quarter-final pairs on the water and ready
to go, a series of violent thunder storms started rolling around
the lake and bouncing off the Swiss Alps to the south.
</P>
<P>
The remaining quarter-finals and the semi-finals should be
completed on Sunday, while the finals are scheduled for Monday.
</P>
