<HEADLINE> Kenyan Loroupe Wins New York Mini Marathon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Kenya's Tegla Loroupe won a
record-tying fifth New York Mini Marathon title in Central Park on
Saturday amid hot and humid conditions.
</P>
<P>
Loroupe, the current world record holder for the fastest full
marathon time, held the lead from the 1.6 kilometers of the 10-km
race and finished in 31 minutes, 37 seconds.
</P>
<P>
"This gives me a lot of confidence about where I am," said
Loroupe, who hopes to compete in the Sydney Olympics later this
year in both the full marathon and the 10,000m events.
</P>
<P>
Current and former Boston marathon champions, Catherine Ndereba
of Kenya and Fatuma Roba of Ethiopia, were second and third
respectively in 32:22 and 32:25.
</P>
<P>
African runners finished in eight of the top 10 positions.
</P>
