<HEADLINE> Belgium Beats Sweden 2-1 in Opening Match of Euro 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Co-hosts Belgium survived a
schoolboy howler of a mistake by goalkeeper Filip De Wilde to beat
Sweden 2-1 in an exciting, incident-filled match that kicked off
Euro 2000 on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Group B match will best be remembered for De Wilde's error
which allowed Johan Mjallby to walk the ball into the net after 53
minutes, bringing the Swedes back into the game after going 2-0
down.
</P>
<P>
Bart Goor of Belgium opened the scoring in the 43rd minute
after seizing a mistake by Swedish defender Roland Nilsson and
Emile Mpenza added the second with a powerdrive in the 46th minute
of the match.
</P>
<P>
Coach Robert Waseige of the Belgian team was pleased with their
performance.
</P>
<P>
He said: "The pressure they put us under was really heavy --
but it proves that we have the mental qualities now to survive
that and win a match." "However, we have to play 30 per cent
better in our next game against Italy and be more composed and
calmer on the ball."
</P>
