<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Belgium Ousts Sweden 2-1 at Euro2000 Opener </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Belgium defeated Sweden 2-1 after
building a 1-0 lead in the Euro 2000 opener and give the co-hosts
a great start to the tournament.
</P>
<P>
The co-host went to a 1-0 lead in the 43rd minute while Bart
Goor beat goalie Magnus Hedman with a low, thunderous shot from 10
meters out, bring the home crowd at the 50,000 capacity King
Baudouin stadium go wild.
</P>
<P>
Seconds after interval, Emile Mpenza took an assist from fellow-
forward Branko Strupar and blasted home, high into the nets of the
luckless Hedman.
</P>
<P>
"It was a very difficult game and we worked very hard." Goor
said after the thrilling win.
</P>
<P>
"We did not start too well and we were a little bit nervous. We
had a lot of problems with Sweden's long ball game." Goor added.
</P>
<P>
Sweden looked down and out, but Belgian veteran goalie Filip De
Wilde made a capital blunder in the 54rd minute, failing to
control the simplest of back passes and allowing Johan Mjallby to
steal the ball and tap it into the net.
</P>
<P>
"It was a back pass from Philippe Leonard but the ball bobbled
at it so I tried to control it.
</P>
<P>
"Maybe the pitch was bit dry. Just stood on it and fell over.
It was like the whole world collapsed." Widle said.
</P>
<P>
But the lead still in hands of the Belgium and in a tense
finish, Patrick Andersson was sent off for a ruthless tackle on
Goor with 10 minutes to go, and together with Sweden's captain,
also went Sweden's chances to force a belated draw.
</P>
<P>
Italy plays Turkey in the other Group B opening game on Sunday.
Lineups:
</P>
<P>
Belgium _ Filip De Wilde; Eric Deflandre, Lorenzo Staelens,
Joos Valgaeren, Philippe Leonard (73, Nico Van Kerckhoven); Gert
Verheyen(87, Jacky Peeters), Marc Wilmots, Yves Vanderhaeghe, Bart
Goor;Branko Strupar (69, Luc Nilis), Emile Mpenza.
</P>
<P>
Sweden _ Magnus Hedman; Roland Nilsson (46 Teddy Lucic),
Patrick Andersson, Joachim Bjorklund, Johan Mallby, Fredrik
Ljungberg,Jorgen Pettersson (50, Hendrik Larsson), Niclas
Alexandersson, Olof Mellberg, Daniel Andersson (69, Yksel
Osmanovski), Kennet Andersson.
</P>
<P>
Referee: Markus Merk, Germany. 
</P>
</TEXT>
