<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chirac to Attend Funeral of Assad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 11 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac will
attend the funeral of Syrian President Hafez Assad to be held
Tuesday, Agence France-Presse quoted an official source at the
Elysee presidential palace as saying Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Chirac will be accompanied by French Foreign Minister Hubert
Vedrine, who has canceled a previously arranged visit to Israel,
Lebanon and Syria scheduled for Sunday and Monday.
</P>
<P>
"The presence of the president of the republic, accompanied by
the foreign minister, in Damascus for the funeral of President
Assad is aimed at expressing the engagement of France in support
of the peace process in the Middle East, at a crucial moment for
the region and in the wake of the Israeli withdrawal from southern
Lebanon," said the same source.
</P>
<P>
"The objective of France is to look for a comprehensive, just
and lasting peace which cannot be made without Syria," it added.
</P>
<P>
It also said that France hopes that Syria will contribute to
the security and stability of the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
