<DOCNO> XIE20000611.0210 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Palestinian Authority Closes Crossing-Point to Revenge Israeli Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, June 11 (Xinhua) -- The Palestinian Authority closed on
Sunday afternoon Karni crossing point, located in eastern Gaza, to
prevent the Israeli goods from entering Palestine self-rule areas.
</P>
<P>
This move is to revenge the strike staged by the Israeli
employees working at Erez Crossing point in northern Gaza, which
prohibited Palestinian workers from getting access to the Israeli
ports to get out their imported goods.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians said they plan to escalate their measures by
closing Erez, Sufa and Rafah crossings and the security crossing
connecting Gaza Strip with the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
A Palestinian source said the value of the Palestinian goods,
which are now in the Israeli ports and cannot be moved to the
Palestinian self-rule areas because of the strike, are estimated at
70 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Karni crossing point is an exit for the Palestinian goods which
are transported between Gaza Strip and the West Bank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
