<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Saudi Crown Prince Meets With Yemeni President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIYADH, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Crown Prince and First Deputy
Prime Minister Abdullah Ibn Abdul-Aziz met in Jeddah on Sunday with
Yemeni president Ali Abdullah Saleh.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the two sides exchanged amicable views and
discussed the bilateral relations, as well as ways of strengthening
them in all fields, Saudi Press Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also discussed the latest developments related to
the Middle East peace process, the Palestinian issue in particular,
the occupied Arab territories and the Arab, Islamic and
international issues.
</P>
<P>
The Yemeni president arrived earlier Sunday in Jeddah.
</P>
<P>
Yemeni Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister Abdul Qader Ba
Jammal had recently said the border dispute between the two
countries will have top priority in the talks between the two
sides. 
</P>
</TEXT>
