<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000611.0212 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Saudi Crown Prince Meets Yemeni President 1st lead-writethru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIYADH, June 11 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Crown Prince and Deputy
Prime Minister Abdullah Ibn Abdul-Aziz met on Sunday with visiting
Yemeni President Ali Abdullah Saleh on relations between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also reviewed the Middle East peace process, Arab
and international issues of mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
But diplomatic sources said here earlier that
the Saudi-Yemeni talks will cover the remaining issues of their
borders demarcation.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia and Yemen need to re-demarcate their land borders
where 300 border signs have disappeared due to denudation and aging
factors.
</P>
<P>
They also have to negotiate a settlement to the demarcation of
their maritime borders in the Red Sea.
</P>
<P>
Senior Saudi officials said earlier this year that following
several years of work of their joint committees in charge of
specifying the borders signs, the two states have succeeded in
relocating most of the land border posts.
</P>
<P>
Saleh arrived in the western Saudi city of Jeddah earlier in
the day on an official visit, which political observers said took
place amidst the positive atmosphere witnessed in the relations
between the two Arab neighbors resulting from a recent visit to
Yemen by Prince Abdullah.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah went to Sana'a on May 21 to take part in the 10th
anniversary of Yemen's unity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000611.0213 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2050GMT, Sunday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS -- Syria's ruling Arab Socialist Baath Party leadership
has decided to nominate Bashar al-Assad, son of the late President
Hafez Al-Assad, as candidate for Syrian presidency.
</P>
<P>
Syrian News Agency on Sunday said the Baath party leadership
made the decision unanimously in a panel meeting Saturday evening.
</P>
<P>
Assad died Saturday of a heart attack at age 69.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Syrian parliament has amended the constitution to pave
the way for Bashar, 35, to succeed his late father who had ruled
the country for three decades. (Syria-Assad-Presidency)
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran's new, reformist-dominated Majlis (parliament) on
Sunday elected Mehdi Karrubi, a prominent radical-turned reformist
leader, as its speaker for a one-year term.
</P>
<P>
Behzad Nabavi, spokesman of the reformist coalition "May 23
Front," and Mohammad Reza Khatami, the younger brother of President
Mohammad Khatami, were elected vice speakers.
</P>
<P>
Karrubi, as the only candidate for the post, won 193 votes out
of a total of 245, with 52 abstentions, in the election of the
Majlis presiding board. (Iran-Majlis-Speaker)
</P>
<P>
DAMASCUS -- A funeral procession for the late Syrian president
Hafez Al-Assad will take place on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The procession will start at 0800 a.m. local time on Tuesday.
The coffin will be carried from the residence in which he lived
during the past three decades to Omaiya Square in Damascus. (Syria-
Assad-Funeral)
</P>
<P>
GAZA -- The Palestinian National Authority closed on Sunday
afternoon Karni crossing point, located in eastern Gaza, to prevent
the Israeli goods from entering Palestine self-rule areas.
</P>
<P>
This move is to revenge the strike staged by the Israeli
employees working at Erez Crossing point in northern Gaza, which
prohibited Palestinian workers from getting access to the Israeli
ports to get out their imported goods.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians said they plan to escalate their measures by
closing Erez, Sufa and Rafah crossings and the security crossing
connecting Gaza Strip with the West Bank. (Palestinians-Crossing-
Closure) 
</P>
</TEXT>
